        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38483",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This does not work like expected:\r\n\r\nIt leads to the problem that \"translate\" throws out exceptions due to \r\n** false locale\r\n** non existing files\r\n** corrupt files\r\n\r\nAll these problems are caught by loading the files before translating.\r\n\r\nLazy loading would also negotate caching.\r\nIt adds a performance problem at translation when using formats which are very excessive like TMX as you delay the loading time into the application time instead of session start.\r\n\r\nAdditionally it would mean that you must traverse the complete directory tree when calling a translation and read all files to know if a translation is available.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-16T07:39:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-16T07:42:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38484",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bonch",
                        "name": "bonch",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Kozlov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "An example: my site on ZF uses 3 (en, de, ru) languages and about 10 files with translations for each language. Basically, I use only one language, for example \"en\". \u041en all pages of my site I see the text in english, until I choose a different language from menu.\r\nSince I need only one language (en), so why do ZF load files for the other two languages? This is overhead IMHO. \r\n\r\nAre there no ways to load only files with necessary translations (en)?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bonch",
                        "name": "bonch",
                        "displayName": "Andrew Kozlov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-16T08:11:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-16T08:11:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38485",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The files are loaded because you say that they all have to be loaded.\r\n\r\nWhy don't you simply define that only the wished language should be loaded?\r\nLook into the manual for details about loading translations.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-16T08:54:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-16T08:54:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38564",
